==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[melior]]''

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/əˈmiːliəreɪt/}}
*{{audio|en-us-ameliorate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|ameliorat|ed}}

#To make better, to [[improve]]; to [[heal]] or [[solve]] a [[problem]].
#:''They offered some compromises in an effort to '''ameliorate''' the disagreement.''

